At the [[2000 United States census|2000 U.S. census]],<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |access-date=January 31, 2008 |title=U.S. Census website }}</ref> 1,541 people, 622 households, and 436 families lived in the town.

The [[population density]] was {{Convert|251.1|PD/sqmi}}. There were 1,875 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|305.6|/sqmi}}. In 2000, there were 622 households, out of which 29.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 54.2% were married couples living together, 8.4% had a female householder with no husband present, and 29.9% were non-families. The U.S. Census Bureau tabulated that 24.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 9.3% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.46 and the average family size was 2.89.

The median income for a household in the town was $33,548, and the median income for a family was $35,517. Males had a median income of $34,000 versus $19,333 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the town was $18,330. About 9.1% of families and 13.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 14.3% of those under age 18 and 12.9% of those age 65 or over.

At the 2019 [[American Community Survey]], there were 2,038 housing units and 214 were owner-occupied; there were 184 families in the town.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 American Community Survey Households and Families|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Grand%20Isle%20town,%20Louisiana%20housing&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1101|website=data.census.gov}}</ref> The average household size was 2.06 for owner-occupied housing units, and the median value of owner-occupied housing units was $203,600.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 American Community Survey Selected Housing Characteristics|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Grand%20Isle%20town,%20Louisiana%20housing&tid=ACSDP5Y2019.DP04|access-date=July 8, 2021|website=data.census.gov}}</ref> Residents of Grand Isle had a median household income of $43,333 in 2019,<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 American Community Survey Financial Characteristics|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Grand%20Isle%20town,%20Louisiana%20housing&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S2503|access-date=July 8, 2021|website=data.census.gov}}</ref> and an estimated 22.3% of the population lived at or below the poverty line.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 American Community Survey Poverty Status|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Grand%20Isle%20town,%20Louisiana%20poverty&tid=ACSST5Y2019.S1701|access-date=July 8, 2021|website=data.census.gov|language=en}}</ref> A year later by the [[2020 United States census]], there were 1,005 people, 330 households, and 184 families residing in the town.

In 2000, the racial makeup of the town was 96.04% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.27% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 0.19% [[African Americans|African American]], 0.19% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.39% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.91% from two or more races. Hispanics or Latin Americans of any race were 1.49% of the population. In 2019, 94.9% of Grand Isle's population were [[Non-Hispanic whites|non-Hispanic white]], 0.8% Black or African American, 2.0% multiracial, and 2.3% Hispanic or Latin American of any race.<ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 American Community Survey Demographic and Housing Estimates|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?q=Grand%20Isle%20town,%20Louisiana%20race%20and%20ethnicity&tid=ACSDP5Y2019.DP05|access-date=July 8, 2021|website=data.census.gov}}</ref> By 2020, the composition was 92.44% non-Hispanic white, 0.2% Black or African American, 1.49% Native American, 0.6% Asian, 2.29% multiracial or some other race, and 2.99% Hispanic or Latino American.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=2020 Race and Population Totals|url=https://data.census.gov/cedsci/table?g=1600000US2230830&tid=DECENNIALPL2020.P2|access-date=December 28, 2021|website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

